text: You just gotta grow and heal and love yourself. And, try not to repeat the same cycle for when you have your own children. But, I can say my Self Love journey has been a huge eye opener for me and taught me a lot. The pain is for the moment but the healing is for a lifetime.

author: Lola🐉
text: They don’t speak on how later on down the line you develop other problems on top of your Mommy/Daddy issues. Such as Depression, Attachment Anxiety, Abandonment Issues, Trust Issues, Emotional Unavailability the list goes on.

author: Lola🐉
text: I accepted my issues a long time ago but it honestly didn’t register to me. Having both of your parents show up physically in your life. And, not show up emotionally nor mentally in life equals up to an absent parent. But, nobody ready for that talk yet.

author: Lola🐉
text: Until you come to common grounds of what the root of your problems are. You’re gonna continuously get hurt by people mentally, emotionally, and physically time and time again because that’s what you’re use to.

author: Lola🐉
text: Healing/Growth is when you finally face your problems. I’m talking the origin of your problems and accepting it for what it is. Mines is I have serious mommy/daddy issues. And, having both of those will really have you going through a lot of pain in your life.
